#. <section class="sutta" id="sn47.36"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn47.36:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 47"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 47"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn47.36:0.2"
msgid "4. Ananussutavagga"
msgstr "4. Not Learned From Anyone Else"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn47.36:0.3"
msgid "36. Aññāsutta"
msgstr "36. Enlightenment"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn47.36:1.1"
msgid "“Cattārome, bhikkhave, satipaṭṭhānā."
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are these four kinds of mindfulness meditation."

msgctxt "sn47.36:1.2"
msgid "Katame cattāro?"
msgstr "What four?"

msgctxt "sn47.36:1.3"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kāye kāyānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, "
"vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of the body—keen, "
"aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world."

msgctxt "sn47.36:1.4"
msgid "vedanāsu … pe …"
msgstr "They meditate observing an aspect of feelings …"

msgctxt "sn47.36:1.5"
msgid "citte … pe …"
msgstr "mind …"

msgctxt "sn47.36:1.6"
msgid ""
"dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke "
"abhijjhādomanassaṃ."
msgstr ""
"principles—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the "
"world."

msgctxt "sn47.36:1.7"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro satipaṭṭhānā."
msgstr "These are the four kinds of mindfulness meditation."

msgctxt "sn47.36:1.8"
msgid ""
"Imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, catunnaṃ satipaṭṭhānānaṃ bhāvitattā bahulīkatattā "
"dvinnaṃ phalānaṃ aññataraṃ phalaṃ pāṭikaṅkhaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"Because of developing and cultivating these four kinds of mindfulness "
"meditation, one of two results can be expected:"

msgctxt "sn47.36:1.9"
msgid "diṭṭheva dhamme aññā, sati vā upādisese anāgāmitā”ti."
msgstr ""
"enlightenment in the present life, or if there’s something left over, non-"
"return.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn47.36:1.10"
msgid "Chaṭṭhaṃ."
msgstr ""
